<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,972,1895,1919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012">Identification.</emphasis>
Resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1865" box="[1115,1291,1895,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pelopidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agna">
<emphasis box="[1115,1291,1895,1919]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012">Pelopidas agna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but lower
</emphasis>
central spots on upper forewing squarish, not linear; an imaginary straight line through two cell spots in male crosses brand near its midpoint; unlike 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pelopidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mathias">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012">Pelopidas mathias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male brand is black; upper hindwing may be pale or spotted; five small spots usually present and one in cell, or none at all on under hindwing; grey patched in dryseason form on underside; female similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pelopidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1013" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1013">Pelopidas agna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[275,527,230,254]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pelopidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1013" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subochracea">
<emphasis box="[275,527,230,254]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1013">Pelopidas subochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
